# Right Click Search Extension - Project Overview

## Project Type

Chrome Extension (Manifest V3) - Customizable right-click context menu search engine manager

## Core Technologies

- **React 19** - UI framework with modern hooks
- **TypeScript 5** - Type-safe development
- **Vite 7** - Build tool with HMR
- **TailwindCSS 3.4** - Utility-first styling
- **Framer Motion** - Premium animations
- **Chrome Extensions API** - Context menus, storage, tabs

## Architecture

### Key Components

- **[Main.tsx](mdc:src/components/views/Main.tsx)** - Primary UI with tab-based organization
- **[SearchEngineCard.tsx](mdc:src/components/search/SearchEngineCard.tsx)** - Individual search engine configuration cards
- **[background/index.ts](mdc:src/pages/background/index.ts)** - ContextMenuManager for right-click menu handling
- **[searchEnginesStorage.ts](mdc:src/shared/storages/searchEnginesStorage.ts)** - Chrome storage persistence layer
- **[useSearchEngines.ts](mdc:src/hooks/useSearchEngines.ts)** - React hook for engine state management

### Data Flow

1. User configures engines in popup UI ([Main.tsx](mdc:src/components/views/Main.tsx))
2. Changes saved to Chrome Storage via [searchEnginesStorage.ts](mdc:src/shared/storages/searchEnginesStorage.ts)
3. Background script ([background/index.ts](mdc:src/pages/background/index.ts)) listens for storage changes
4. Context menu dynamically updates with enabled engines
5. User right-clicks → selects engine → new tab opens with search results

## Design Philosophy

- **Vision OS Inspired**: Glassmorphism, backdrop blur, translucent backgrounds
- **Minimalist**: Clean, uncluttered interface
- **Tab-Based**: Separate Text Search and Image Search engines
- **Inline Editing**: Direct field editing without modals
- **Instant Feedback**: Real-time sync between UI and context menu
